    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDef">Definitions:\n
• Common Divisor: divides all given numbers.\n
• G.C.D.: largest common divisor.\n
• Relatively Prime: G.C.D. = 1.\n
• L.C.M.: smallest common multiple.</string>

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryProperties">Relatively prime numbers have these properties:\n
1. If a number is divisible by two relatively prime numbers, it’s divisible by their product.\n
2. If ab is divisible by c and b, c are relatively prime, then a is divisible by c.</string>

